topic: Melbourne business rejects Israeli woman over origin

ideas.title: The Lygon Street Lament
ideas.premise: An Israeli tourist tries to order a 'parma' at a Lygon Street Italian restaurant, but the waiter refuses service because she's not 'authentically Italian' enough.
ideas.why_funny: Plays on Lygon Street's reputation for Italian food and absurd levels of authenticity.

ideas.title: The Quantum Quandary
ideas.premise: An Israeli quantum physicist attempts to use Quantum Brilliance's new Melbourne foundry, but is denied access due to 'uncertainty' about her origins.
ideas.why_funny: Combines cutting-edge science with the absurdity of discrimination, using a pun.

ideas.title: The Cup Day Catastrophe
ideas.premise: An Israeli woman tries to place a bet on the Melbourne Cup, but the bookie refuses, claiming her 'foreign' luck would ruin the odds for everyone else.
ideas.why_funny: Uses the Melbourne Cup's high stakes and superstitious betting culture for comedic effect.

ideas.title: The Power Bank Paranoia
ideas.premise: After the Melbourne Airport power bank incident, a business lounge bans all Israelis, fearing their tech is 'too hot to handle'.
ideas.why_funny: Exaggerates a recent news event into a ridiculous overreaction based on prejudice.

ideas.title: The MedEx Mishap
ideas.premise: An Israeli doctor arrives at the MedEx launch in Melbourne, only to be told they're 'fully staffed' and don't need her expertise, hinting at discrimination.
ideas.why_funny: Understated humor highlighting the irony of a medical event rejecting a qualified doctor.
